1. Binance adjusts the monitoring labels of 10 currencies including ARDR, and removes the seed labels of 3 currencies including JUP;
2. First Digital: FDUSD is returning to the $1 anchor;
3. Du Jun: A token will be publicly selected every month to invest $2 million to $10 million, and the judgment basis will be shared with the community;
4. AI interaction protocol Wayfinder launches new badges for PRIME holders;
5. Arthur Hayes: Trump's tariff plan may force the Federal Reserve to restart loose monetary policy;
6. FDT: It has cooperated in withdrawing funds, but the funds were frozen due to AML and KYC issues;
7. Justin Sun: A $50 million reward is provided to law enforcement agencies and insiders who can provide effective assistance;
8. FDT: Justin Sun can't produce any evidence to prove his accusation;
9. Justin Sun: It is recommended that stablecoin project parties do not choose Hong Kong trust institutions;
10. FDT responded to Justin Sun's accusation: This is a typical smearing behavior, and FDT will take legal action;
11. North Korean hacker Lazarus Group 12 hours ago transferred 40.78 WBTC sold in exchange for 1,857 ETH;
12. StakeStone has opened an airdrop query website;
13. Trump invited Salvadoran President Nayib Bukele to attend a White House meeting on April 14 to discuss bilateral cooperation and diplomatic relations;
14. Binance launched Spot Block Matching large-volume transaction solution;
15. Binance Alpha launched STO;
16. Babylon announced token economics: total 10 billion, community incentives accounted for 15%;
17. The US dollar index DXY fell below 102, the first time since October last year.
